Most people hate arts, it seems like doing an artwork is really a challenge or problem just because they’re not talented on that. But you know what? Trying different things won’t make us a less person. Even though it’s hard we should try it, be inspired and motivated for you to continue your artwork. There are a lot of process and we will see ourselves enjoying on things that we don’t really like in the past.

 

To be honest, doing my own artwork is a mess, but as I continue to put   effort and produce something new, I am able to get the output I want. Teach ourselves to discover new things and it will improve our both internal and external growth.

 
 

“You get whatever accomplishment you are willing to declare because if you don’t do it someone else will.”

 
 

Title: Love: Place Where You Can Go

Date Created: February 17, 2021

My frottage is about places where you can go especially with your love ones. In every problem and challenges we face every day; we need to unwind sometimes and we really deserve it. Make ourselves comfortable and have some privacy.

 

Doing this artwork is easy for me because I have experience in the past. During elementary days we’re always doing it during our free time. I remember, we used to make a bet who will make the most amazing frottage. Also, we have a given topic so we’re able to do the activity at the exact time. And since valentines’ day is one of the unforgettable celebration we have, we can relate about it. We can feel the love and care we have from each other. It’s so fulfilling knowing that “love” came first to every one of us.

 

 

 
 

Title: Soul

Date Created: April 1, 2021

I can say that this self-portrait is really a challenge for me. You can see that the subject I use is myself. Even though it’s not exactly what my face looks like, I’m happy because I have the chance to draw myself and share my skills. This artwork entitled “Soul” is the best artwork for me that I have and this will be a stepping stone, a great journey for me to pursue in the near future.

 

For me, doing self-portrait isn’t easy, there are a lot of preparation for this kind of artwork. To be honest, I’m so afraid to try this because I don’t have any experience and to draw is not my hobby. But of course, I tried my best even though there are a lot of mistakes. I know practice makes perfect and I’m willing to take those mistakes just to do better and improve my own skills. I believe that as time goes by, all of those hard work will paid off.

 

 

 
 

Title: Love: The Pathway

Date Created: March 30, 2021

From the title itself, you can see that my 3D artwork is about the pathway. I draw this because sometimes I don’t know where I’m going in life. There are a lot of what ifs in my mind that can’t be answer by now. But I know in the near future I’ll take the right path for myself, for my own growth and for my own peace. I will just go with the flow and trust the process.

 

I can say that this kind of artwork will test your patience. If I’m not mistaken, I repeated it 7 times because I can’t get the correct angel of my artwork. I don’t know if it’s the artwork itself or the way I take picture of it. Also, I can’t decide what will be the object or concept I’ll use.  B­ut with the help of video tutorial, I came up with a good concept and the outcome is so amazing.

 

 
 
  

 

Kyla Gonzales
